              <article class="comment-pick">
          <header>
            <span class="ars-avatar" style="color: #82b1ff; background-color: #1565c0;"><img class="ars-avatar-image" src="https://cdn.arstechnica.net/civis/data/avatars/m/1/1002.jpg?1668794168" srcset="https://cdn.arstechnica.net/civis/data/avatars/m/1/1002.jpg?1668794168 1x, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/civis/data/avatars/l/1/1002.jpg?1668794168 2x" alt="Aurich" /></span>

            <div class="text-base font-bold sm:text-xl">
              <a class="text-gray-550 hover:text-gray-400 dark:text-gray-300 dark:hover:text-gray-400"
                href="https://arstechnica.com/civis/members/aurich.1002/" target="_blank">Aurich</a>
            </div>
          </header>

          <div class="comments-pick-content">
            A note for iOS users:<br />
<br />
iOS remembers your zoom levels for websites, and it will not reset them just because we changed the site design. So before you play with our text setting options you might want to verify that you're set to 100% zoom first, because if you enlarged the text on our old design a long time ago and forgot that setting can still be there.<br />
<br />
If you forget how to do it, tap the box with underlines icon up at the top left, in the URL field, and then the zoom size will briefly show at the bottom of your screen, before being replaced by A A buttons to shrink or enlarge the copy. (This is latest iOS, it's similar but slightly different in previous versions if you're not up to date.)
          </div>

          <div class="comments-pick-timestamp">
            <a href="https://arstechnica.com/civis/posts/43268228/" target="_blank">
              <time
                datetime="2024-10-29T21:08:53+00:00">October 29, 2024 at 9:08 pm</time>
            </a>
          </div>
        </article>
              <article class="comment-pick">
          <header>
            <span class="ars-avatar" style="color: #82b1ff; background-color: #1565c0;"><img class="ars-avatar-image" src="https://cdn.arstechnica.net/civis/data/avatars/m/1/1002.jpg?1668794168" srcset="https://cdn.arstechnica.net/civis/data/avatars/m/1/1002.jpg?1668794168 1x, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/civis/data/avatars/l/1/1002.jpg?1668794168 2x" alt="Aurich" /></span>

            <div class="text-base font-bold sm:text-xl">
              <a class="text-gray-550 hover:text-gray-400 dark:text-gray-300 dark:hover:text-gray-400"
                href="https://arstechnica.com/civis/members/aurich.1002/" target="_blank">Aurich</a>
            </div>
          </header>

          <div class="comments-pick-content">
            I'm being told that several other browsers remember your text settings, so in general you might want to be sure you're reset to 100% before you play with the text settings or they might not act quite as expected.
          </div>

