          <div class="comments-pick-content">
            <blockquote class="xfBb-quote" data-name="HydraShok">Thank you! I do see that now. I had been looking for the text icon in Nate's screenshots in the article (which I still do not see).<br />
<br />
<a href="https://arstechnica.com/civis/attachments/94555/">View attachment 94555</a></blockquote>Here's how the text settings work: They're right by the text, in a somewhat obvious and hard to ignore place. When you open them you can see your changes happen live, and then hit the X to close it again. Or, you can press the button at the bottom:<br />
<br />
<a href="https://arstechnica.com/civis/attachments/94558/"><img src="https://cdn.arstechnica.net/civis/data/attachments/51/51080-f517054fb716b4c19203409675b76982.jpg" alt="1730241266207.png" /></a><br />
<br />
That will move the icon up to the nav bar, where it's much easier to miss, but is available should you ever want it. And get the settings out of your way for daily reading.<br />
<br />
Basically we have an &quot;obvious mode&quot; and &quot;power user mode&quot;. Once you know how to set things you can dismiss it for any infrequent use later.
          </div>

